content.description: Start sitting, matched down and left of Cindy Swank on the obvious left facing sidepull/pinch feature. Move right using small sidepulls and interesting movement until you are on Cindy Swank. Save some juice for the somewhat difficult moves pulling up and over the lip.
content.protection: A couple of pads and a spotter.
content.location: Start sitting on the northwest corner of the Honey Boulder. Same start as Christine Keeler (v5).

content.description:
Start standing towards the right side of the overhanging west face on a good crimp rail. Move slightly left then up using small crimps and core tension. Once you hit the good hold on the lip, match and move right and up using a small crimp on the lip and a good hold that is hard to see from below.

One of the holds pulling up and over is a hollow flake that looks like it could break off, so be gentle...
content.protection: A couple of pads and a spotter.

content.description: Classic V2!  Follow the rightward leaning crack on good crimps and incuts to a slopey bucket at the lip.  Worth a stop before heading down to Jedi Mind Tricks.

Start sitting on the large left facing sidepull/pinch feature. Make a hard move up and left to a good dish. Continue up the arete using nice holds to a huge sloper jug. Pull onto the ledge above. This problem has fun movement and good holds on some pretty crappy rock.
content.location: Same start as Swanky Sit. Climbs the arete

content.description: Start standing on good holds about five feet up. Move up through a decent crimp to a big hold below the lip. Grab a good crimp on the lip then pull through some difficult moves to top out.
content.protection: A couple of pads and a spotter.
content.location: On the left side of the slightly overhanging west face. Start on good sidepulls about five feet up.
